                            <comment id="12434638" author="gmarziou" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2006 10:19:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moreover, it is not possible to change the user/password from the procrun monitor GUI.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test scenario:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;launch tomcat5w.exe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click on the &quot;Log On&quot; tab&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;set user/password&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click OK&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;launch again tomcat5w.exe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click on the &quot;Log On&quot; tab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;==&amp;gt; Your settings have not been taken into account and the service is still using local system account.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12450478" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2006 18:24:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The --User and --Password as well as GUI for setting them are not used for setting the user for the service.&lt;br/&gt;
The are used for setting the username other the local system if the Run mode is &apos;java&apos; not &apos;jvm&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In case of the &apos;java&apos; run mode, procrun launches the separate process (java.exe) and the username&lt;br/&gt;
used for running this process is the one supplied with those directives.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For setting the user used for running the service itself use the Control Pannel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12450714" author="gmarziou" created="Fri, 17 Nov 2006 12:25:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Mladen for this explanation, it covers my initial report but it does not cover the test scenario I put in my 2nd comment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;launch tomcat5w.exe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click on the &quot;Log On&quot; tab&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;set user/password&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click OK&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;launch again tomcat5w.exe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;click on the &quot;Log On&quot; tab: your settings have not been saved.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;So, here I think that even if I did not understand the purpose of this user/password at first, there is still a problem with the GUI which does not save my settings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you want me to open a new bug?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12481931" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sun, 18 Mar 2007 12:21:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in the SVN.&lt;br/&gt;
Although the correct usage is --ServiceUser and --ServicePassword&lt;br/&gt;
The binaries can be found at:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/tomcat/tc6.0.x/trunk/res/procrun/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/tomcat/tc6.0.x/trunk/res/procrun/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
